title: Sticky Clarence
description: Everything Clarence comes into contact with sticks to his body - a pen, a can of beans, even one of his chickens! Eventually, Clarence becomes the center of a big ball of objects.

title: Lonely Lonnie
description: Clarence, Jeff, and Sumo record themselves telling scary stories in the treehouse.

title: Clarencio Magnifico
description: Clarence performs a magic act for some of Aberdale's senior citizens.

title: Dream Boat
description: Sumo devotes himself to the Sisyphean task of building a boat, defying the expectations of everyone in his life, including himself.

title: Attack the Block Party
description: Clarence, Jeff and Sumo investigate a high school party down the street, which they mistake for an alien invasion.

title: Hit the Piñata  Music Video
description: Sing along to this pinata song written by Simon Panrucker.

title: Separation Anxiety
description: After talking, passing notes and throwing pencils at the ceiling in class, Ms. Baker separates Clarence and Sumo. They devise ways to communicate to each other from across the room in a series of gags.

title: Birding with Guyler
description: Guyler spends a day bird watching in Bendle Park - and makes a new special friend.

title: Big Boy
description: In order to get them to notice he's more mature, Clarence draws chest hairs on himself and decides to show them off!

title: Claw Machine
description: At the Pizza Swamp arcade, Clarence convinces passerby Vu to use his skills to free Clarence from the claw machine.

title: Bird Boy Man
description: Sumo discovers an injured roadrunner, names him Hot Sauce, and nurses him back to health. The two become inseparable pals, but Sumo learns that a wild animal can't be contained.

title: Clarence Gets a Girlfriend
description: When Clarence is asked out on a date by Ashley, a girl in his class, he realizes he doesn't know the first thing about having a girlfriend! Clarence enlists Sumo and Jeff to transform himself into the perfect gentleman just in time for his big date.

title: Doodle Battle
description: Clarence and his pals find a large piece of paper and have fun doodling on it.

title: Plane Excited
description: Clarence is all excited visit his grandma when he learns that Chad has never been on a plane. Clarence makes it his mission to help Chad get through a hectic flight.

title: Time Crimes
description: When Clarence is convinced he has the power to manipulate time he vows to only use his abilities for good. However, a day at school puts his morals to the test when he's given the ultimate choice to help his friends or pause time in the name of fun.

title: Escape from Beyond the Cosmic
description: When Clarence accidentally breaks a local arcade game Jeff has become obsessed with, Clarence puts together his own real-life version of the game at home, encouraging Jeff to act out his fantasy in levels created exclusively by Clarence.

title: Freedom Cactus
description: Clarence draws a comic for the school paper and it becomes a huge hit with the kids. When angry parents step in and censor the comic's crass humor, Clarence must stand up for his artistic vision.

title: Belson Touch
description: After learning about King Midas' gold touch during a lesson about Greek Mythology, Clarence daydreams about having a Belson touch that turns anything he touches into Belson.

title: Percy in Have a Ball
description: Naive Percy invites his strangely quiet classmate Gilben over to play, and to show Gilben his prized ball collection.

title: Valentimes
description: When Clarence notices his teacher Ms. Baker is the only one in class left without a Valentine this year, he decides to enlist the help of Sumo to set her up with Sumo's teacher, Mr. Mozer! Will sparks fly or will the boy's naive view of romance backfire?

title: Ren Faire
description: Clarence and his pals venture to the Aberdale Renaissance Faire. Clarence confuses a medieval play for reality, and vows to stop the evil black knight from getting the princess.

title: The Interrogation
description: After Mr. Reese discovers his precious car smeared with meatball sauce, he pulls out his officer's cap and enlists Clarence to help his investigation to nab the culprit.

title: Saturday School
description: After creating an unapproved mural on a wall at Aberdale Elementary, Clarence, Jeff and Sumo are forced to come to school on a Saturday to clean up as punishment.

title: Rainy Day
description: Clarence and his friends play in the rain and enjoy their cozy evenings with family.

title: Pretty Great Day with a Girl
description: Clarence and Amy, a unique girl from down the street, bond over a hunt for a monster-sized rock called an "erratic."

title: Belson Gets a Girlfriend
description: Clarence is in disbelief when he learns his best friend Belson has a new girlfriend named Pipi. But when he observes their less than romantic behavior, he decides that he needs to teach them the ways of love to help keep their fling afloat!

title: Lost Playground
description: When Aberdale Elementary's beloved playground equipment is replaced with safe, boring alternatives, Clarence and the gang seek out their old playground equipment in the legendary lost playground yard.

title: Beans
description: Clarence attempts to wake a sleeping dog.

title: Beauford T. Pusser
description: Inspired by the short Every Child, an oprhan ktten is passed from kid to kid until it finally makes its way to Ms. Baker, who names him Beauford T. Pusser.
